Feb. 4th, 2019

Overview
- You can learn the basic information of power plants in the U.S. from the "Power Plants of Your State" app.
- The app is created based on EIA power plants dataset.
- The app is running on yiapplege.shinyapps.io.
- Codes can be found in yiapplege's github.
- This pitch takes MA and all energy sources as an example.

How to use:
1. Choose your state.
2. Check all the energy sources that you are interested in.
3. Enter the number of plants you want to see.
4. Click the "Let's go!" button.
5. View the results in 3 tabs: Data, Plot and Map.
6. Click the "Download the Data" button if you want to save the dataset.

Results - Plot

This tab shows the total power capacity over years grouped by energy source.

Results - Map

This tab shows the location of all chosen power plants by leaflet map.
